Description: GetchaBooks is a textbook price comparison service that helps students save time and money when buying their books.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: GetchaBooks is a free textbook price comparison service that helps students save time and money when buying their books. GetchaBooks was founded in the spring of 2010 by three college students. They were frustrated by the expensive prices at their school bookstore, but also couldn't stand the unreasonable time commitment required for online price comparison shopping. They created GetchaBooks to provide a textbook buying experience that combined the simplicity of the former with the savings of the latter. Students enter their school and what classes they're taking. GetchaBooks looks up what books they need from online course lists, performs price comparisons across a number of online booksellers, and recommends how they can get their books as cheaply as possible. GetchaBooks uses an intelligent recommendation engine to generate these suggestions, taking factors like savings on combined shipping into account.
Founders: Michael Lazer-Walker, Michael White, Richard Mondello

Full Description: Hello Human! We're a small and idealistic company based in a northwest suburb of Chicago, 4 people to be exact. We were born out of our common desire to replicate change. We did not particularly like how the success of Facebook has made all of us do less and seem like we do more. So instead of just complaining and bitching, we listened to all of you who agree with us and came up with a solution. So here's how it works. Using our mobile app called "My Dailies", you create a group (say "Lisa's Situp World) and invite your friends to the group. You then each create dailies for that group (say "Just did 50 situps!"). Advertisers bid on keywords in the group names (in this case likely "Situp"). Each time you do a daily, the advertiser pays and 50% of that ad revenue goes towards a KickStarter.com project that we have personally selected.  When that KickStarter project gets funded or we simply find something else more interesting, we switch to another one. The other 50% goes to the 4 of us to pay our electricity bill and maybe some fresh organic apples. This is going to be so awesome. Welcome to Be Good Today. You are the future of change.

Description: Stand Offer is a search engine enabling investors to discover crowdfunding startups.
Full Description: Search for crowdfunding startups to invest in. Standoffer is crowdfunding's Hotels.com and soon to be Scottrade. You can search for crowdfunding startups to invest in across the industry by location, category, numerous financial figures, project goals, and more.  Currently in beta testing until the SEC releases their crowdfund investing regulations (expected Summer 2013) Standoffer is poised to make as big a splash as anyone, offering the most practical solution to finding startups worth investing in among the tens of thousands on the web. What is Crowdfunding? Crowdfunding is a form of online fundraising for individuals and startup companies, experiencing rapid growth in route to becoming the web's fastest growing industry in 2012. To raise money, users post a campaign describing their project goals and plans for raised funds. What investors receive in return for investments is determined by which crowdfunding portal the campaign is posted on.  Worldwide, the most popular type of portal is equity-based, where investors receive equity or shares in startups for funds. The most popular type of portal in the U.S. however is rewards-based, where donors receive kickbacks or 'rewards' for donations such as products pre-release and/or memorabilia.  History:  The popularity of rewards-based portals was due to investment laws in the United States unintentionally making equity-based crowdfunding in the U.S. illegal. However in April of 2012, the JOBS Act was signed into law by President Obama, legalizing equity-based crowdfund investing whenever the U.S. Securities & Exchange Commission (SEC) released their new regulations for the industry. The SEC was yet to release the regulations as of March 2013. Despite the delay, tens of thousands of campaigns and nearly 600 crowdfunding portals have gone online, causing many to become virtually invisible among the crowd.  Another surge of portals and campaigns is expected with the release of the SEC's regulations, making the task of finding every startup worth investing in nearly impossible. Luckily for investors, Standoffer.com enables simple and easy navigation among the sea of crowdfunding sites and startups with searches by your own preferences including by location, goals, figures, and more. Welcome to Standoffer, Welcome to Crowd Control.™

Description: Zebra Digital Assets employs encryption and key management architectures to facilitate the safe exchange of an organization's data.
Full Description: Protecting your information is our business, but your information is none of our business! At Zebra Digital Assets, our goal is to empower your most valuable asset: your data. We believe only YOU should have complete control over your data. That’s why we designed our products with two main ingredients: The most powerful encryption and key management architectures available today, with the flexibility to upgrade into the future. A passion to simplify. Zebra can extend the reach of your existing tools beyond business boundaries, without IT involvement. Zebra started with a very basic idea: Security should help you share information, not get in the way. Yet everywhere we look, we see examples of security being a barrier, not an enabler. Zebra enables you to protect your information simply, conveniently and effectively, and share it with anyone securely. Sharing information is a simple concept, yet there is no simple solution for sharing outside the security perimeter. The perimeter only protects what is inside, and does not protect information shared outside. Zebra’s simple tools protect your information at all times, no matter where it travels. A ZPS file (Zebra Portable Safe) works through the entire lifecycle of a document – creation, sharing, modification, storage, retrieval, and destruction or expiration. less

Description: Computer Network Solutions (CNS) is a young engineering contracting firm located in the high-tech hub of Winston-Salem, North Carolina.
Full Description: Computer Network Solutions (CNS) is a young engineering contracting firm located in the high-tech hub of Winston-Salem, North Carolina. Owners Jim Reynolds and Jamie Frederick have a total of almost 40 years of experience in connectivity and network engineering. The budding economic recovery is bringing rapidly increasing opportunity for the installation of high-end warehouse management systems, and CNS is very well positioned to capitalize on the growing need of companies that wish to better manage their inventory in order to stay competitive. Jim Reynolds was senior engineer for the Special Modification Services of CDS Energies, one the country's leading producers of Automatic Data Collection (ADC) products, and one of his primary responsibilities was to travel to customers' warehouse sites and perform custom wireless network modification using CDS products. Jamie Frederick has been a senior engineer for the Symbol Networking Equipment system installation services for the past 9 years. Among her responsibilities were custom wireless installation of Symbol networking equipment and ADC products at customers' warehouses. Shortly after Computer Network Solutions was formed, it executed outsourcing agreements with both CDS Energies and Symbol Networking to provide custom network installation services to their customers.  Winston-Salem is an ideal location for such a business.  Forces magazine recently ranked it as the 9th best place in the U.S. for business and careers in 2001 with economic drivers fed by the city's continued dominance as a center for arts, financial services, tourism, and education. The area includes home bases for companies such as RJReynolds, Wachovia, Krispy Kreme, HanesGlobalBrands, Homes Fine Foods, and ISPN Sports. Winston-Salem is also a leader in the nanotech, high-tech, and bio-tech fields, and medical research is an expansively-growing local industry. Overall, it is an ideal location for Computer Network Solutions to build its future.
